!! What it does

The cytoscape engine plugin provides an alternative rendering backend for [[tw-graph|$:/plugins/flibbles/graph]]. It replaces vis-network with [[Cytoscape.js|https://js.cytoscape.org/]] (v3.33.2) while keeping the same `<$graph>` widget API — all existing graph markup works unchanged.

!! Key features

* ''Drop-in replacement'' — switch engine in tw-graph settings, existing `<$graph>` markup works as-is
* ''Interactive clusters'' — drag a node onto another to group them visually, double-click to rename, color picker
* ''Per-graph cluster config'' — each graph stores clusters in its own config tiddler (like positions)
* ''Nested clusters'' — clusters inside clusters
* ''Visual drag feedback'' — cluster border turns orange→red as a node approaches the ejection distance
* ''COSE layout'' — physics simulation that handles compound node groups natively
* ''Blur debouncing'' — stable popup interaction (200ms debounce prevents popup flicker)

!! How clusters work

Clusters are named visual groups — not tiddlers. They exist only in a config tiddler as JSON.

|!Action |!Gesture |
|Create cluster |Drag node A onto node B → auto-creates "Cluster #1" containing both |
|Add to cluster |Drag node onto existing cluster container |
|Remove from cluster |Drag node far away from cluster (200+ px from grab point) |
|Rename cluster |Double-click cluster label → inline text input |
|Change cluster color |Double-click cluster → color palette below name input |
|Nest clusters |Drag one cluster container onto another |
|Delete cluster |Remove all members → cluster auto-deletes |

!! Prerequisites

* `$:/plugins/flibbles/graph` (tw-graph) v1.6.0+
* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+

